events.title: ASAC Meeting re Epstein resources
events.description: A meeting scheduled by the FBI's New York field office to discuss resources related to the Jeffrey Epstein case.

keyFacts: The FBI was still actively holding meetings and allocating resources related to the Jeffrey Epstein investigation in November 2020, over a year after his death.
The meeting was organized by and involved personnel from the FBI's New York field office.
The calendar entry shows the meeting was considered a priority (Priority: 5) and had a reminder set.
All individual names of FBI personnel involved are redacted in the document.
